_ww-text_text.en: Groups of designed components that get you started.
Complete screens ready to use or customize.
Small, reusable UI elements that serve as the foundation.

This UI library provides a structured set of reusable components, blocks, sections, and pages optimized for use within WeWeb. Built with scalability and maintainability in mind, each element supports customizable properties, responsive design, and optional logic bindings. The library is intended to accelerate frontend development in WeWeb by offering clean, modular, and extensible UI patterns ready for integration into real-world projects.

The library is not opinionated per se, but it is built based on how I normally would build components for my projects. If you do not agree, or need extended functionality, you can always go into the component and make your own customization (it is encouraged!) but the library will get you very far in its base configuration.

Can't wait to see what you build with it!
Documentation on how to use KMUI with WeWeb.
The smallest, most atomic units. buttons, inputs, toggles, badges, etc. These are fully customizable and can include state, bindings, and logic. Ideal for building up more complex interfaces.

Each category serves a specific role from low-level elements with full logic support to fully assembled layouts. This makes it easy to build scalable, maintainable frontends with consistent design and behavior without starting from scratch.
Pre-built layout areas for content. A designed layout ready for use. Such as App headers, navigation bar, sidebar layouts. You can use this as starting points for building your layouts.
Composable groups of components in a design. Such as menus, cards, forms. Blocks encapsulate layout and behavior for repeatable UI patterns, often with dynamic content or interactivity.
Fully designed pages. Also for inspiration. Copy them or build on them.
Create a brand new project for your thing.
Interaction roundness determines the radius of your interaction items. This include buttons, input fields, select boxes, tabs.
Interaction height determines how tall your interaction elements are. These include buttons, (single) input fields, select boxes, tabs

_ww-text_text.en:
All elements in KMUI uses default font. Change your project font and it will be applied to all.
Color library also contains its own Text folder, which holds text color.

Note:
"s" is used as the application font size for most things; "strong" is the normal strong text color.
"body is mostly used for longer form text. Color text-body is mostly used for longer form text.
Card roundness determines the roundness of your cards and sections.
Content width sets the max width of your body content area.

To accelerate setup, KMUI supports rapid theming via WeWebs library settings. Adjusting global tokens such as colors, typography, and spacing automatically propagates those changes across all components. For granular control, individual components remain fully editable, allowing you to override styles, structure, and logic as needed.

Use the "template" above to see how changes affect your UI library.
You can change anything to your desire but here are some pointers to where to start.
Accent color is used as your brand color. It's used for highlighting important Interaction elements and selections. Set dark and light seperately.
